UPDATE fishspecies SET description='Latin name, Silurus glanis. Originally introduced to the country in 1880. Catfish have grown in popularity and can now be caught in a variety of waters around the UK and are accessible to most. Fish have now grown to much larger sizes, although the British record was frozen in October 2000 at just 62lb.', baits='Halibut pellets, Roach, Squid', method='Livebaiting, Deadbaiting' WHERE _id='23';
UPDATE fishspecies SET description='Latin name, Anguilla anguilla. Snake like in appearance, the eel is one of the few coarse fish to be eaten within the UK. Though the population is currently at high risk due to disease and pollution, combined with the complex breeding process that involves mature eels swimming across the atlantic to the Sargasso Sea to spawn. Specimen sized eels are thought to have become trapped in lakes and canals and are unable to migrate when spawning time comes. The British Record stands at 11lb 2oz. While a fish over 4lb is considered a specimen.', baits='Deadbait, lobworms', method='Free-running rig' WHERE _id='12';